# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Ascent — environment variables
# Copy to .env.local and fill in. Everything is optional: with no keys at all,
# Ascent runs in deterministic "mock" mode — fully functional, just without
# LLM-written nuance.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Which LLM backend to use:
#   gemini     -> Google Gemini       (LOCAL DEV & TESTING — recommended here)
#   bedrock    -> AWS Bedrock/Claude   (PHASE 2 / production, enterprise privacy)
#   claude-cli -> local `claude` CLI   (LOCAL EVAL — uses your Pro/Max subscription)
#   mock       -> deterministic, keyless
#   auto       -> (default) gemini if a key is present, else mock
# Keep this as `gemini` locally; set to `bedrock` in production env.
LLM_PROVIDER=gemini

# ── claude-cli provider (local eval via subscription) — see docs/CALIBRATION.md ──
# Requires the `claude` CLI installed + logged in (claude /login). Spawns it headlessly;
# uses your subscription, NOT pay-per-token, as long as ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is unset.
# CLAUDE_MODEL=sonnet           # or opus, or a pinned id like claude-sonnet-4-6
# CLAUDE_CLI_PATH=claude        # override if not on PATH
# CLAUDE_CLI_TIMEOUT_MS=120000

# ── Gemini (local dev) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Get a key at https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=
# Optional: override the model (default gemini-3-flash-preview; GA: gemini-3.5-flash)
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-3-flash-preview

# ── AWS Bedrock (Phase 2 / enterprise) ───────────────────────────────────────
# Uses your standard AWS credentials (AWS_PROFILE / AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID + SECRET,
# or an IAM role on Vercel/AWS). Default model is the latest Claude Sonnet (4.6)
# via the US geo inference profile (data stays in-US, works in us-east-1).
# BEDROCK_REGION=us-east-1
# BEDROCK_MODEL_ID=us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6
#   alternatives: global.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6  (max throughput)
#                 eu.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6      (EU residency)

# ── GitHub (optional) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Raises API rate limits for public scans. Fine-grained token, read-only
# "Contents" + "Metadata".
# GITHUB_TOKEN=

# ── GitHub App (private repositories) — see docs/GITHUB_APP.md ───────────────
# Lets users install Ascent on their org to scan private repos via short-lived
# installation tokens. Requires DATABASE_URL. Public scans don't need this.
#
# Permissions the App needs, by feature:
#   • Scanning private repos        → Contents: read, Metadata: read, Pull requests: read
#   • PR maturity gate (checks/comment) → Checks: write, Pull requests: write
#   • Practice "open starter PR"    → Contents: write, Pull requests: write
# Webhook events to subscribe to: Installation, Pull request, Push.
# GITHUB_APP_ID=
# GITHUB_APP_SLUG=ascent-maturity
# GITHUB_APP_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
# Base64-encoded PEM (recommended) or raw PEM with \n escapes:
# GITHUB_APP_PRIVATE_KEY=

# ── GitHub OAuth (sign-in) — see docs/GITHUB_APP.md §4 ──────────────────────
# Reuse the SAME GitHub App's Client ID + a generated client secret, so a signed-in
# user's token can list THEIR installations. Set the App's Callback URL to
# {host}/api/auth/callback. AUTH_SECRET signs the session cookie (any long random string,
# e.g. `openssl rand -base64 32`). When unset, the app runs without sign-in (pages open).
# GITHUB_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=
# GITHUB_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=
# AUTH_SECRET=

# ── Autoscans + live intelligence (enterprise) ──────────────────────────────
# Vercel Cron hits /api/cron/rescan (see vercel.json). Set a secret to protect it;
# Vercel sends it as `Authorization: Bearer <CRON_SECRET>`.
# CRON_SECRET=
#
# Regression alerts (Feature: live intelligence). After an autoscan or a push-triggered
# re-scan, Ascent diffs the new report against the prior one; on a regression (level demotion,
# slide into "ungoverned", or a material score drop) it POSTs a Slack-compatible message here.
# Unset = alerts are computed + audit-logged but not dispatched. A Slack incoming-webhook URL works.
# ALERT_WEBHOOK_URL=
#
# Public base URL of this deployment — used to build absolute links in alerts + PR check
# "details" URLs (e.g. https://ascent.yourco.dev). Falls back to relative links when unset.
# ASCENT_PUBLIC_URL=

# ── Database (Phase 2 — not used by the MVP) ─────────────────────────────────
# Local dev: point at the docker-compose Postgres (see docker-compose.yml).
# Production: point at your Aurora DSQL cluster (Postgres-compatible).
# Aurora DSQL has no local emulator, but a perpetual free tier (100k DPU + 1GB/mo).
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://ascent:ascent@localhost:5432/ascent
# DSQL_ENDPOINT=
# DSQL_REGION=us-east-1
